The list of female presidential aspirants for the 2023 general elections continues to rise as Revered educationist, Prof. Benedicta Egbo joins the race. Set to formally declare her intention on Monday in Asaba, Delta State, the educationist who is contesting on the platform of the National Rescue Movement (NRM) believes that “It is time to rescue the nation from poor leadership, unite the citizenry and build a strong, virile, progressive and equitable democratic society.” According to her, “the 2023 general election provides another opportunity for the populace to elect credible leaders who will provide dividends of democracy and not carnage as obtainable today.” -Advertisement- In a statement, a group, Prof. Egbo For President Support Group explained that: “For long, Nigerians have been denied and deprived of their basic fundamental rights as enshrined in the 1999 constitution as amended. Security and welfare of the people are mere mirages as no part of the country is secured from terrorists, insurgents, bandits, kidnappers and ritual killers.” The group also stressed that she “will effectively address this national embarrassment and make Nigeria great again.” The statement added that the educationist who is also the chairperson of National Rescue Movement, North America, will “leverage on her wealth of experience and global goodwill to salvage Nigeria and redirect the ship of the nation to the path of dignity, honour, prosperity and advancement, … as well as provide the much needed compassionate leadership that will uplift the people’s standards of living if voted into office.” It stated that the party is a mass movement strongly determined to provide progressive governance and return power back to the people on who sovereignty resides. Professor Benedicta Egbo (PhD) is a Professor of Education in Canada. She was born in Kano and hails from Onicha-Ugbo, Aniocha North LGA, Delta North Senatorial District, Delta State.